https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0UgfN8vB.title: Spicy Peanut Butter Noodles :: Super Easy 3 Minute Recipe
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0UgfN8vB.description:
*** Please refer to the TIP at the bottom of the expected questions.


It was made quickly in 3 minutes, but it tastes like the skill of a professional.
It can be made quickly without complicated roasting process,
Peanut butter is added and you can enjoy it in a different taste.


*** Weighing is scale (g), rice spoon (Tbsp), and teaspoon (tsp).

[1 serving]
✤ Ingredients
  - 210g Udon noodles
  - 7g (1Tbsp) Soy sauce
  - 5g (1tsp) Oyster sauce
  - 16g (1Tbsp) Peanut butter (sugar-free or low-sugar)
  - 3g (1tsp) Sugar
  - 2g (0.5Tbsp) Roasted sesame seeds
  - 4g (1tsp) Minced garlic
  - 3g (0.5Tbsp) Chili powder
  - 14g (2Tbsp) Noodle water
  - 18g (3Tbsp) Vegetable oil (avocado (recommended), grapeseed oil, etc)
  - 2 Tbsp Chopped green onion

✤ Toppings
  - Chopped green onions
  - Roasted sesame seeds

✤ TIP
  - You can substitute 1Tbsp of soy sauce instead of oyster sauce
  - Instead of peanut butter, finely grind 1Tbsp of roasted sesame seeds and put them in. Of course the taste is different.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BV7B78jC.description:
Zippo Lighter Restoration - Making a Wooden and Epoxy Lighter Case. In this video I restored an old Zippo lighter and made a case for this Zippo, out of wood and Epoxy resin.
This zippo lighter is quite old. I bought it for restoration from a person who found it with the metal detector on a beach. This zippo is made of brass and the sea water created a beautiful patina but if I had not restored it now, it would most likely have been destroyed in a short time. 

The restoration of the zippo lighter was not difficult because I used original parts for repair. But after I finished restoring I thought of making a wooden and Epoxy resin case. I have never seen this project anywhere so I had to make my own plan. For the case I used curly Koa wood. I will leave you a link at the end of the description. It was quite difficult to mill the slot where the lighter had to go.

I tried in this restoration process to film the steps that I followed quite simply to understand by you, but if you have questions about the restoration, I am at your disposal in the comments category.

Also, during the restoration I used subtitles about the process and solutions used. If you notice grammatical errors, I apologize in advance. English is not my native language and I am doing my best to improve it.

I put a lot of passion and effort into this restoration. Although I was afraid of the results of the case, I am proud of how it came out and I really like it. I hope you like the restoration and the construction of that case.
That's all for this project, enjoy watching and I have to focus for the next restoration.
